<h1>@HI{{zo}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @EM{{@HI{{zo}}}}.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{zo}}}} is a sentence ending particle that adds force to a sentence. It indicates a command or threat or
adds force to a sentence.
In this latter usage, it is more emphatic than <a href="grammar-particle-ze.html">ze</a>.
It is mostly used by men.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{sorosoro@KJ{{meeting^deliberation}}wo@KJ{{commence}}meru@EM{{zo}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Let's get the meeting under way.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{stubborn^long}}ru@EM{{zo}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I can do it!
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

